The paper discusses the design and control of soft robotic systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The methodology proposed involves the representation and calculation of generalized forces, which is related to control systems (cs.SY) and mechanical engineering (cs.ME). The use of fiber-reinforced elastomeric enclosures (FREEs) as actuators is a topic in electrical engineering (cs.ET) and materials science (cs.EM).
